#DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS('derivatives', 'critical points', 'minimum,maximum')
#  Find 2 critical point of a cubic polynomial and determine
#  whether the polynomial increases or decreases on the intervals
#  involving the critical points.
#ENDDESCRIPTION

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$b1 = random(6,10,1);
$coef3 = 2;
$coef2 = 3*($a1+$b1);
$coef1 = 6*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = random(1,11,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = -$coef3 x^3 + $coef2 x^2 - $coef1 x + $coef0 \). This function has two critical numbers \(A<B\):
$BR
\( A = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $a1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f'(x) \)
is positive (type in \(+\)) or negative (type in \(-\)).
$BR
\( (-\infty, A) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "-";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (A,B) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "+";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (B,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "-";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
Thus \(f(x)\) has a local \{ans_rule()\} at \(A\) (type in MAX or MIN)
END_TEXT
$ans = "MIN";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
and a local \{ans_rule()\} at \(B\) (type in MAX or MIN).
END_TEXT
$ans = "MAX";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
